  "prompt": "What is reliance jio?",
  "response": "Reliance Jio, officially known as Jio Infocomm Limited, is a telecommunications company in India that is a subsidiary of Reliance Industries Limited. Launched in September 2016, Jio is known for its significant impact on the Indian telecommunications market by providing high-speed 4G LTE services at very competitive prices. \n\nKey features of Reliance Jio include:\n\n1. **Affordable Data Plans**: Jio revolutionized the telecom sector in India by offering data at extremely low prices, which led to a massive increase in data consumption across the country.\n\n2. **4G Network**: Jio was one of the first companies in India to provide a nationwide 4G LTE network, which allowed users to access high-speed internet services.\n\n3. **Free Trials**: Upon its launch, Jio offered free trials that included unlimited voice calls and texts, along with free data, which attracted millions of subscribers.\n\n4. **Wide Range of Services**: Jio offers a variety of services including voice calling, messaging, and various digital services such as JioTV, JioSaavn, and JioCinema, among others.\n\n5. **Rapid Subscriber Growth**: Jio quickly gained a large customer base, becoming one of the largest mobile network operators in India within a few years of its launch.\n\n6. **Focus on Digital Ecosystem**: Jio has been instrumental in promoting digital services in India, contributing to the growth of the digital economy.\n\nReliance Jio continues to expand its services and infrastructure and has played a crucial role in making internet access more affordable and widespread in India.",
